last_episode_to_air.name: Two Funerals and a Wedding
last_episode_to_air.overview: JJ and Sugar's joyous celebrations turn into a morbid affair after the gang learns of some sad news.

name: Brassic
overview: A group of working-class friends finding unconventional ways to win at life in northern suburbia. These lads have dealt, scammed, bribed and conned their way through adolescence, but now, on the brink of adulthood, their dealing and stealing is catching up with them and a whole load of trouble is heading their way.

seasons.name: Series 3
seasons.overview: In the last series of Brassic, we were left with a cliff-hanger: What did Erin whisper to Vinnie? With pressure building from the police and crime boss Mr. McCann, Vinnie is forced to ruthlessly take no prisoners in his bid to escape. It’s a hectic world of bulls, snakes, kidnappings, betrayal, and this time, a full-size horse...

seasons.name: Series 4
seasons.overview: With all the Brassic gang back in Hawley, things don’t get any easier. From discovering severed body parts to training racing dogs, then finding unexpected guests and causing mayhem at a murder mystery night, trouble is never far away when Brassic comes to town.

seasons.name: Series 5
seasons.overview: Reeling from the dramatic events of the series 4 finale, Vinnie and the gang face big repercussions from their entanglements with the dangerous McDonagh brothers and powerful drug buyer Manolito.

seasons.name: Series 6
seasons.overview: After an epic end to the last season, the gang are back with as much wild adventure and hilarity as ever. Reeling from the explosive encounter with Manolito, they set about getting their lives back in order. Only now the landscape is changing, people are getting older and the question of growing up looms in the air. But what does 'growing up' mean to a bunch like this?

episodes.name: Your Pony's A C...
episodes.overview: Vinnie's plan to steal a tiny horse is thwarted by a jar of chloroform and a pigeon.

episodes.name: Big Sandy's Funeral
episodes.overview: Needing cash for stripper Big Sandy's funeral, the lads decide to rob her boss's safe - but plans go awry when they get trapped in a sewer.

episodes.name: The Fight
episodes.overview: A rival traveller challenges Ash to a fight. But Vinnie gets suspicious when Ash ends up in hospital.

episodes.name: The Fish
episodes.overview: Desperate to pay back McCann, the boys agree to help a woman get revenge on her ex-husband.

episodes.name: Ronnie Croft
episodes.overview: A raid on a weed farm goes wrong when Erin's brother turns up and someone accidentally gets kidnapped.

episodes.name: Antique Dildo
episodes.overview: Vinnie nicks a car containing McCann's stolen antiques and must find the thief or face dismemberment.

episodes.name: The Circus
episodes.overview: Vinnie has been hiding out in his weed shed since faking his own death to escape from local gangster Terrance McCann. Tommo and Erin need his help and try to lure him out of hiding with a new business proposition and together with the lads they plot to rob a travelling circus. With the help of a disgruntled clown, Mr Popov, the gang aim to make this theft a 'roaring' success.

episodes.name: A Nice Day Out
episodes.overview: Vinnie is tasked with collecting a guy called Tony Tillerton. It seems like a simple task... Meanwhile, a booze cruise to France is under way.

episodes.name: Antique Hunters
episodes.overview: Vinnie agrees to grow weed on an industrial scale for McCann and the lads get busy setting up a new grow shed. Meanwhile, Erin attends a disastrous dinner party with Jake's family and Tommo hatches a plan to steal some erotic furniture to re-vamp the Rat & Cutter. But what starts as a simple robbery quickly descends into bedlam when a rival gang of thieves turn up and the lads find themselves joining an elaborate treasure hunt.

episodes.name: The Intruder
episodes.overview: Suffering from insomnia, Vinnie decides to have a chilled night in at the local pub, but things take a sinister turn when a stranger breaks in.

episodes.name: The Festival
episodes.overview: Ordered by McCann to sell all the weed they have grown, the lads decide to throw a music festival in Jim's field.

episodes.name: Stealing a Wedding
episodes.overview: When a close friend gets engaged, Vinnie is determined to throw them the best wedding he can muster, and so decides to steal one.

episodes.name: The Great Bull Semen Heist
episodes.overview: Vinnie finally gets released from prison and with the newly promoted Detective Carl Slater watching his every move, he is doing his best to lie low.

episodes.name: Gideon's Mum Funeral
episodes.overview: Vinnie's friend Gideon calls to say his mother has passed away and asks Vin to help him honour her final wishes.

episodes.name: The Ransom
episodes.overview: Ashley's cousin Doolan has been kidnapped and his uncle Francis calls on Vinnie to be the bag drop man in his ransom.

episodes.name: Classic Cars
episodes.overview: Mr and Mrs Bishop are back and the gang are once again caught up in their bitter divorce battle.

episodes.name: Parenthood
episodes.overview: When Ashley decides that he wants to track down his real father, Vinnie and the gang promise to do everything they can to help find him.

episodes.name: The Keithy Problem
episodes.overview: Erin's brother Ronnie returns to Hawley claiming he has turned over a new leaf. Erin reluctantly convinces farmer Jim to let him stay in his spare room, but it's not long before Ronnie and his con mate Keithy cause total havoc.

episodes.name: Bees
episodes.overview: The gang are in a buzz when Vinnie is tasked by Chinese Dan to steal some beehives, so the lads scope out a nearby village famous for making local honey.

episodes.name: The Shack
episodes.overview: Driven mad with worry, Erin has told Vinnie about the money she owes McCann. But when McCann's men kidnap Tyler as a warning, Vinnie is so furious that he kidnaps McCann's twins in retaliation and the situation worsens.

episodes.name: Getting There
episodes.overview: The gang is back and ready to hit the road for Ringo and Babs' Welsh wedding, while Vinnie gets wind of Erin's hiding place and uses the road trip as an excuse to get her back.

episodes.name: Day at the Dogs
episodes.overview: The gang sees a cash cow with a retired racing greyhound, but a mystery begins when the animal finds a human foot during training.

episodes.name: Lost in the Woods
episodes.overview: What should have been a fun, lads-only camping trip turns into a nightmare when the gang end up horrendously lost.

episodes.name: Exotic Zoo
episodes.overview: When Manolito, Davey MacDonagh's eccentric distributor, offends Vinnie, the gang decide to get revenge by raiding his exotic zoo.

episodes.name: Amy
episodes.overview: A young woman claims to be Erin’s half-sister, but is she telling the truth? The gang attempt to steal a rare and valuable rose.

episodes.name: Saint Erin (Murder Mystery)
episodes.overview: After a tip-off from Dr Chris, Vinnie and the gang don some fancy dress and join a posh murder mystery evening at a stately home to gain access to its cellars stocked with valuable vintage wine.

episodes.name: An Unexpected Guest
episodes.overview: Vinnie befriends an elderly woman who is hiding from Davey MacDonagh. Can the gang get their new friend to safety without Davey finding out?

episodes.name: Davey's House
episodes.overview: Having let their prisoner slip through their fingers, the MacDonaghs are on the war path and convinced that the gang had something to do with it.

episodes.name: Eddie
episodes.overview: A chaotic 24 hours as the gang takes an unlikely hostage and escorts him on his bizarre round of errands.

episodes.name: Missing Body
episodes.overview: A World War II-era bunker gets uncovered near Jim and Shirley's farms, but the discovery leads to a catastrophic encounter with an old land mine and lands the gang in trouble with the MacDonaghs again.

episodes.name: Hans
episodes.overview: Tommo gets the surprise of his life when a young German man shows up looking for him.

episodes.name: Sweet Sixteen
episodes.overview: Erin's dad dies, leaving her with a debt to the local honchos, so the gang do what they do best to get the money - some cheeky thievery.

episodes.name: Ratcatcher
episodes.overview: A ratcatcher is hired to help with Jim's rat problem, but it is soon clear it's him who needs help.

episodes.name: Caravan of Courage
episodes.overview: A caravan with some precious cargo goes missing and the gang are tasked with getting it back.

episodes.name: Albert
episodes.overview: A giant bunny, a crocodile and a golf buggy chase - Cardi goes on a mission that'll truly test his mettle.

episodes.name: The Manolito Problem
episodes.overview: In their biggest heist yet, the gang steals some rare Lowry paintings.

episodes.name: Stolen FA Cup
episodes.overview: Vinnie meets a seasoned criminal with something interesting stashed in his attic - the original FA Cup from 1895 stolen by his Grandad.

episodes.name: That Night
episodes.overview: All is finally revealed when the gang revisit what happened THAT night with Manolito.

episodes.name: Blast from the Past
episodes.overview: Farmer Jim is forced on a trip down memory lane when an old flame pops up in Hawley. Also - JJ is back!

episodes.name: Naked Cult
episodes.overview: Tommo meets Craig, a once-famous dance arcade champion, as the gang try to rescue Gideon from a naked cult.

episodes.name: Heartbreak
episodes.overview: Cardi's mum shows up in Hawley - she is getting married.... again. Meanwhile, Carol gets a nasty shock of her own.

episodes.name: The Mark
episodes.overview: After being humiliated by some local youths, Ashley decides it's time to up his game - with the help of Jim and Cardi.
